    "Since remote sensing images' highly complex spatial pattern and geometric structure, classification is severely hampered by redundant background.",
    "Furthermore, the variety of items makes classification more challenging.",
    "However, the intricate spatial patterns and geometric structures inherent in remote sensing images pose challenges to classification due to redundant backgrounds and a myriad of objects, contributing to significant intra-class variability and limited inter-class variety.",
    "Due to variances in optical properties such as geometry, size, texture, and orientation of the ground objects, scenes in the same semantic category frequently exhibit significant visual disparities in remote-sensing-based image classifications.Different imaging circumstances can result in significant radiation intensity and colour changes in scenes of the same kind.",
